==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|do}} + {{term|good}} + {{term|-er}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{derogatory}} One who [[advocate]]s or performs what they believe to be the [[morally]] [[superior]] course of action, even in the face of overwhelming experience or factual evidence that its effect is only irrelevant or harmful.
#: ''The Prohibition Act in the United States was an unsuccessful attempt by '''do-gooders''' to save people from the dangers of alcohol, whether they wanted to be saved or not.''

